### English Title:
Kremlin Announces Delivery of Putin's Message to Trump Ahead of Ukraine Talks

### English Text Summary:
The Kremlin announced that Steve Witkoff, a U.S. envoy, delivered a message from Russian President Vladimir Putin to President Donald Trump before upcoming talks on Ukraine in Paris. Kremlin spokesperson Dmitry Peskov expressed hope that the discussions would focus on achieving a peaceful resolution. He mentioned that President Trump had been informed about a recent conversation between Putin and Witkoff. Peskov criticized Europe for continuing to focus on the war rather than seeking peace. U.S. Secretary of State Marco Rubio and Witkoff are set to meet with Ukrainian officials in Paris to bolster Ukraine's defenses against ongoing Russian aggression. The article notes that while Trump's promise to end the war quickly seems unrealistic, hopes for a ceasefire by Easter are also dimming as Russia intensifies its attacks on Ukraine.

